# Statsig Docs — Cursor Rules

This is the Statsig documentation repo at https://docs.statsig.com, powered by Mintlify. Full AI instructions are in `CLAUDE.md` — read it before making any edits.

## Quick reference

- **Framework:** Mintlify (not Next.js, no build step)
- **Files:** `.mdx` only — never `.md`
- **Local dev:** `mintlify dev` (install once with `npm i -g mintlify`)
- **Navigation:** `docs.json` → `navigation.tabs[].groups[].pages[]`
- **Snippets:** must live in `/snippets/` — import with `import X from '/snippets/...'`
- **Links:** root-relative, no extension: `/feature-flags/overview`
- **Spellcheck:** add new terms to `styles/config/vocabularies/Mintlify/accept.txt`

## Callout syntax (Mintlify MDX — NOT Markdoc)

```mdx
<Note>...</Note>
<Info>...</Info>
<Tip>...</Tip>
<Warning>...</Warning>
```

## Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Required"
description: "Recommended for SEO"
sidebarTitle: "Optional shorter sidebar label"
---
```

## When editing docs

- Apply Statsig style rules: active voice, present tense, second person, contractions, sentence-case headings.
- Use `.cursor/rules/edit-doc.mdc` for the full style checklist.
- For feature coverage audits, use `.cursor/rules/feature-comparison.mdc`.

## Do NOT modify

- `scripts/kapa.js` and `scripts/statsig.js` — analytics tracking
- `docs.json` theme, colors, logo, or font settings
